I have so many great classes coming up in April and I’m especially excited for this special Saturday afternoon birthday cake fundraising class on 4/15! @godslovenyc cooks and home-delivers nutritious, medically tailored meals for people too sick to shop or cook for themselves in the NYC area. It is a non-sectarian organization serving people living with severe and/or chronic illness, and their children and caregivers. All of their services are provided free to clients and full of love. In 2022 they delivered 3.2M+ meals, having served nearly 11,000 individuals, and having worked with 13,500 volunteers. They’re on track to deliver an additional MILLION meals this year for a total of 3.4 million! It’s an incredible organization doing important work. I am a longtime supporter of GLWD and love their annual Birthday Bake Sale which is a fundraising campaign that highlights the fact that they send every single client (and every child and caregiver) a personalized birthday cake every year. Join me to bake the actual GLWD birthday cake recipe (!!!!!) All proceeds from this class will go to GLWD. Let’s make some cake and raise some money! Class is sliding scale, starting at $10 (which covers a meal for one client). Learn more/see them in action at @godslovenyc + www.glwd.org/bake sale. All class info + signup link is at juliaturshen.com/classes 🧡🎂 #BirthdayBakeSale

I have loved to cook since I was a little kid. Feeling empowered in the kitchen has made a big difference in my life. I hope to share this feeling with young cooks in my special Kids Cooking! class this SUNDAY AT 2pm EST!!! We will make English muffin pizzas, homemade ranch dip that we can dip cucumbers into, and a loaf of chocolate chip ice cream bread. We will learn about flavors, safe chopping, and the magic of baking! All ages welcome (and only one ticket per device needed, so if a kid + a caregiver are attending together, no need to buy 2 tickets). Depending on age, experience + kitchen confidence, an adult might be needed to help (grocery shopping, turning on the oven, getting things in + out of the oven, slicing cucumbers, etc.). I will walk through every single step slowly and answer every question. This is going to be FUN!!!!!

Today I’m participating in #Bake4BeTheMatch2023 spotlighting the US national marrow organization @bethematch! There are many ways to support:
-SIGN UP for FREE for the registry if you’re between ages 18-40 (link in my bio). Only about 1 in 430 people on the registry go on to be a donor, and if asked to donate, it’s similar to giving blood. It is imperative to build the registry to ensure more matches for people who need them! **Anyone can be a donor to anyone in the world through partnership organizations, so this is truly an international effort!🌍🌏🌎 
-DONATE to provide financial assistance for uninsured portions of medical costs for patients who need it (click the “Support Me” button through the link in bio)
-SHARE this post in stories, highlights, and on your grid to amplify the search 🗣Make sure to include the link in my bio!
…………….
People are matched through HLA proteins which are most similar in people of the same ethnicities and ancestral backgrounds. Many BIPOC populations are underrepresented on the registry. Odds of finding a match based on ethnicity are as follows: Black 29%, Asian 47%, Latinx 48% and White 79%. A HUGE goal of our campaign is to diversify the registry and increase those odds for all, and especially for our dear friend, food entrepreneur, and co-host @winniesbakery. The health inequality is real and absolutely unacceptable.

Check out the hashtag #Bake4BeTheMatch2023 to see all the yummy contributions from the participants, and a special thanks to @jenthecakept, @savorandsage, and @winniesbakery for organizing this collab! Feel free to DM any of them with questions or for more information!

SUMMER GAME CHANGER! IT’S CORN! 🌽🌽 Thank you @adamsfairacrefarms for posting this + teaching me this cool trick. Microwave 3 ears of fresh corn in their husks for 6 minutes (sounds like from the comments that less time works for many too - figure out what works for you! Less time for less ears). Carefully cut off the stem end. Push the corn out (I use a towel because it’s hot!) - it comes out beautifully clean, no annoying corn silks + it’s perfectly cooked. This is the most exciting thing. Corn!
